{
  "texts": [
    "Concerning in-vehicle switches, positioned as general network devices, there is an expectation for enhanced versatility.",
    "These switches are anticipated to support protocols like TSN IEEE 802.1Qav, IEEE 802.1Qbv, and others, while also accommodating top-level Software-Defined Networking (SDN) or SOA scheduling designs.The deployment of technologies like TSN and SOA on embedded platforms underscores the critical role of automotive software architecture and design.",
    "Different embedded platforms, such as Microcontrollers (MCUs) or System-on-Chips (SoCs), exhibit distinct bottom-layer operating systems like Linux or QNX, AUTOSAR architecture for Central Processing (CP) or Application Processing (AP), and middleware for SOME/IP or DDS.",
    "These diverse platforms necessitate unique software frameworks for effective design and performance optimization.",
    "Cost and Performance OptimizationCost and performance are critical to E/E architecture."
  ]
}